[2] France ex Spain
Date: Tue 27 Feb 2018
Source: Toulouse Infos [in French, trans. Corr.SB, edited]
http://www.toulouseinfos.fr/actualites/29080-chu-de-toulouse-appelle-a-vigilance-apres-cas-de-rougeole-region.html


The Toulouse University Hospital calls for vigilance after cases of measles in the region. Up to 12 cases of this disease identified in Agen in high school students after a school trip to Spain.

Measles is a highly contagious viral infection. The symptoms are high fever, cough, rhinitis and conjunctivitis, followed by rash. Be careful, this is not a mild illness.

The Toulouse University Hospital recalls some simple principles concerning this disease. The symptoms can begin at any time from 7 -- 18 days after being in contact with the person with measles. The hospital reminds that in case of doubt it is necessary to consult your doctor quickly.

