[3] Greece
Date: Fri 2 Mar 2018 20:57
Source: Ekathimerini [edited]
http://www.ekathimerini.com/226323/article/ekathimerini/news/measles-cases-on-the-increase


The measles outbreak in Greece is showing no signs of slowing down, with the Center for Disease Prevention and Control (KEELPNO) saying [Thu 1 Mar 2018] that there have been 1829 recorded cases since last May [2017].

The center said the number of cases has doubled in the first 2 months of the year [2018], compared with 922 reported in late December [2017].

According to KEELPNO, there have so far been 3 measles-related deaths in under a year.

Roma children make up around 70 per cent of cases while the rest are mostly people aged between 25 and 44 who have either not been vaccinated or who may have had their 1st shot but never followed up with the 2nd.

