[4] Pakistan
Date: Thu 2 March 2018 2:26:10 PM
Source: MENAFN [edited]
http://menafn.com/1096540036/Pakistan-Measles-epidemic-claims-third-life-in-Upper-Dir


As many as 4 children have died due to outbreak of measles in Katan Payen and Charkom areas of district Upper Dir during the last couple of days, raising concerns among the villagers. According to local residents, a 2 year old minor girl died on [Fri 2 Mar 2018] in Katan Payen area. Three more children have died in the past few days in the 2 villages including 2 sons of one, Waheedullah.

The deaths of 4 kids raised concerns among the local residents who demanded of the health authorities to immediately send teams to the affected areas so that the epidemic could be controlled before it could claim more lives.

Meanwhile, district health officer Iftikhar-ud-Din has said that medical teams had been sent to the 2 villages, adding the affected children were being provided medical facilities.

